<memory_lifecycle>
This project uses a 3-tier memory lifecycle. Read [INDEX.md](file://./.agent-memory/INDEX.md) first.

| Tier | Location | Purpose |
|------|----------|---------|
| 1 - Plans | `docs/plans/` | Implementation plans (create before large changes) |
| 2 - Findings | `.agent-memory/project.md` | Issue logs, bug causes, architectural discoveries |
| 3 - Standards | `.agent-memory/workflows.md` | Finalized deployment rules, API standards, conventions |

When finishing a task:
- Log discoveries in `project.md` (tier 2) following the format in `AGENTS.md`.
- If a pattern becomes a permanent rule, promote it to `workflows.md` (tier 3).
</memory_lifecycle>

<coding_rules>
- **Surgical Edits**: Focus only on the requested files. Never refactor unrelated files.
- **Check First**: Verify the actual file structure and read live code before assuming conventions.
- **No Hardcoded Secrets**: Load credentials from environment variables. See [.env.example](file://./.env.example).
- **Documentation**: Maintain existing comments and docstrings intact.
</coding_rules>
